Signal.Description:
Status from Motion Control while executing a path:
- path_id
- segment_index
- status: {IN_PROGRESS, REACHED_GOAL, COLLISION_EMERGENCY_STOP, PATH_INVALIDATED, PLANNING_FAILURE}
- second_run_result (if in SECOND_RUN context): {UNDEFINED, SUCCESS, FAILURE}
Mission Control uses this to determine when to transition between states and to set final second-run status.

Grid map queries performed while selecting targets:
- get_cell_state(row, col) - returns {UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED}
- get_neighbors(row, col) - returns up to 4 neighbor coordinates and their wall segment states
- get_wall_state(edge_descriptor) - {UNKNOWN, PRESENT, ABSENT}
- get_reachability_info (optional) to ensure candidate frontiers are reachable (may delegate to Path Planner).

Events enqueued to system event queue:
- event_type: {EXPLORATION_COMPLETED, EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT}
- timestamp_ms
- map_complete_flag
- cause: {MAP_COMPLETE, GLOBAL_TIMEOUT}
MC consumes these to transition states.

To Motion Control:
- avoidance_maneuver_request:
    * type: {STOP_AND_TURN, ARC_TURN, SLOW_DOWN}
    * desired_heading or turn_angle
    * priority: {EMERGENCY, AVOIDANCE}
- emergency_stop_request: command to override all motion and set both motor speeds to 0.

Component.Execution:
- Implements a main loop with period T:
  while (system_running) {
    t_start = get_system_time_ms();
    1) Sample sensors through Sensor Abstraction (CMP--10).
    2) Update Pose (CMP--11) using differential drive kinematics and current motor commands.
    3) Call Mapping (CMP--6) to update map from new sensor data.
    4) Update Exploration Status / Time Limit (CMP--4).
    5) Advance Mission Control FSM (CMP--1).
    6) If required by MC state, call Planner (CMP--5) to compute or update paths.
    7) Call Motion Control (CMP--12) to compute new motor_set commands and send to motor interface.
    t_end = get_system_time_ms();
    dt = t_end - t_start;
    Sleep until next cycle start to maintain period T.
  }
- Ensures ordering of responsibilities per cycle as specified in requirements.

Data.Content:
Cell and Wall Enumeration Types (language-agnostic):
- enum CellState { UNKNOWN = 0, FREE = 1, BLOCKED = 2 };
- enum WallState { W_UNKNOWN = 0, PRESENT = 1, ABSENT = 2 };
- enum MissionState { IDLE=0, EXPLORE=1, RETURN_TO_START=2, SECOND_RUN=3, COMPLETED=4 };
- enum PathStatus { SUCCESS=0, NO_PATH=1 };
- enum PathExecutionStatusEnum { IN_PROGRESS=0, REACHED_GOAL=1, COLLISION_EMERGENCY_STOP=2, PATH_INVALIDATED=3, PLANNING_FAILURE=4 };
- enum SecondRunStatus { NOT_RUN=0, SUCCESS=1, FAILURE=2, ABORTED=3 };
